    • Method Detail

      • lookup

        Set<IEntityModifier> lookup(org.bukkit.entity.EntityType type)
        Look up all of the possible modifiers for the given entity type.
        Use lookup(EntityType, Class) if you know the type; it returns a parameterized object instead of a generic.
        Parameters:
        type - the type to search for
        Returns:
        a set containing all of the possible modifiers

      • lookup

        IEntityModifier lookup(org.bukkit.entity.EntityType type,
                       String label)
        Look up a modifier for a given entity type by using its label (IEntityModifier.getLabel().
        Use lookup(EntityType, String, Class) if you know the field type; it returns a parameterized object instead of a generic.
        Parameters:
        type - the type to search for
        label - the label of the modifier to be returned
        Returns:
        the modifier, or null if nothing matched the given parameters

      • lookup

        <T> Set<IEntityModifier<T>> lookup(org.bukkit.entity.EntityType type,
                                   Class<? extends T> field)
        Look up all of the possible modifiers for the given entity type that have a specific field type. For Optional- wrapped fields, see lookup(EntityType, Class, boolean).
        Type Parameters:
        T - the field type
        Parameters:
        type - the entity type to search for
        field - the class representing the type of the field to search for
        Returns:
        a set containing all of the possible modifiers

      • lookup

        <T> IEntityModifier<T> lookup(org.bukkit.entity.EntityType type,
                              String label,
                              Class<? extends T> field)
        Look up a modifier for a given entity type by using its label (IEntityModifier.getLabel()) and the field type. For Optional-wrapped fields, see lookup(EntityType, String, Class, boolean) .
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the field to be returned
        Parameters:
        type - the entity type to search for
        label - the label of the modifier to be returned
        field - the class representing the type of the field to be returned
        Returns:
        the modifier, or null if nothing matched the given parameters

      • lookup

        <T> Set<IEntityModifier<T>> lookup(org.bukkit.entity.EntityType type,
                                   Class<? extends T> field,
                                   boolean optional)
        Look up all of the possible modifiers for the given entity type that have a specific field type. Optionally get modifers that are wrapped with an Optional<>.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the field type
        Parameters:
        type - the entity type to search for
        field - the class representing the type of the field to search for
        optional - whether or not to return Optional-wrapped fields
        Returns:
        a set containing all of the possible modifiers

      • lookup

        <T> IEntityModifier<T> lookup(org.bukkit.entity.EntityType type,
                              String label,
                              Class<? extends T> field,
                              boolean optional)
        Look up a modifier for a given entity type by using its label (IEntityModifier.getLabel()) and the field type. Optionally get modifers that are wrapped with an Optional<>.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the field to be returned
        Parameters:
        type - the entity type to search for
        label - the label of the modifier to be returned
        field - the class representing the type of the field to be returned
        optional - whether or not to return an Optional-wrapped field
        Returns:
        the modifier, or null if nothing matched the given parameters
